OL,3,CGirl's sudden death prompts family's
OL,4,Cfight for nationwide heart screenings
OL,6,F"You go from getting out of the shower
OL,7,Fgetting ready for a family day out and
OL,8,Fthen two hours later you're being
OL,9,Fasked which funeral director you
OL,10,Fwant," said Carly.
OL,12,FThe traumatic experience is one shared
OL,13,Fby parents Steve and Gill Ayling from
OL,14,FScunthorpe after Gill found her son
OL,15,FNathan unresponsive on his bed back in
OL,16,F2019.
OL,18,FThe 31-year-old died from an
OL,19,Fundetected arrhythmia back in 2019.
OL,20,FThe condition, his family say, could
OL,21,Fhave been detected with a #70 ECG scan.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/8
